defaultJust over 40% of households in the Broadwindsor Parishes have at least one person who would like to use public transport. One of th
defaulte big issues in my campaign was to get the bus reinstated for Greenham and Drimpton residents. (1)  
defaultCommunications to try and get the 99 bus service to return to Greenham and Drimpton. defaultLetter dated 2
defaultnd
default January 2013
defaultMr Williams set out his reasons why the
default No. 99 bus service was withdrawn. He states “The Chard to Yeovil route does not carry enough passengers to be self- sustaining.”  He goes on to say that Somerset County Council, “decided not to divert the service into Drimpton because Drimpton is within D
defaultorset, and therefore the responsibility of Dorset County Council to cover.” (2)
defaultThe implications of this letter suggest the following:
defaultA. The bus company have decided it is not economic to run the service through Greenham and Drimpton. One lady told me tha
defaultt a bus driver that works for the company told her that it was not getting enough people using it. 
defaultB. The Somerset County Council do not feel obliged to offer a service which goes into Dorset.
defaultPoint A does not make sense.  The bus stops short of the villa
defaultge and travels along the road that links Lyme Regis with Crewkerne. There are 3 farms and 4 houses along the two mile stretch. If the bus was to come into Drimpton it would still travel 2 miles before linking up with Clapton as it does now. The difference 
defaultis some 200 dwellings.  There are a substantial minority of citizens in Drimpton and Greenham who are over the age of 70 years. Many of them need to visit their doctor in Crewkerne. To do so, if they do not drive a car, they have to pay a taxi company to t
defaultake them at a cost. 
